Business Analyst		Real Capital Analytics		Greater New York City Area		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><p>The business analyst is a line-of-business departmental expert who bridges the gap between the technical team and business team during the implementation of a decision management solution. </p><p>  </p><p>The BA collaborates with business experts to model the business domain, create business use cases, define the business rule vocabulary, and manage decisions based on business rules and events. BAs also work with developers to design decision management solutions, author and test business and event rules, and implement decision governance processes. </p><p>  </p><p>The BA will work within RCA’s newly-created Continuous Analytics team, nested in the technology department. A successful BA will be able to design, analyze, test, and review the processes and business rules governing RCA’s data. Additionally, the BA will produce sophisticated analysis that will determine the business decisions regarding how data is managed and displayed in client-facing products. An understanding of the domestic and international commercial real estate market will be helpful in this position, but not necessarily a prerequisite. </p><p> </p></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"></div>